{
  "text": "Let us assume that a bodily distortion occurs within a particular entity. He then has a choice of seeking allopathic aid or experiencing a catalyst of a distortion and not seeking correction of a distortion. Can you comment on two possibilities for this entity and his analysis of each path? I am wrong if the entity is polarized towards service to others. Analysis properly proceeds along the lines of a consideration of which path offers the most opportunity for service to others for the negatively polarized entity. The antithesis is the case for the unpolarized entity. The considerations are random and most likely in the direction of the distortion towards comfort.",
